<paragraph blockId="43.[264,1322,284,1270]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
Etymology. I am pleased to name this species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blahnik Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2005" box="[881,992,1164,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Alterosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paprockii">
<emphasis box="[881,992,1164,1189]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">paprockii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for Henrique Paprocki, my good friend and fellow trichopterist, who collected the 
<typeStatus box="[942,1044,1204,1230]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen of this very unusual species.
</paragraph>
